<li>Therefore , the phosphorylation rate ofArcA was 3.7 times faster in the presence of the metabolite .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8226939" target="_blank">8226939</a>]<br></li>
<li>The RR-bound 32P was stably retained for the A1 group RRs such as pArcA , pCpxR , pCusR , pKdpE , and pNarL but was rapidly released for the A2 group RRs , including pBaeR , pCheB , pCheY , pCreB , pDcuR , pNarP , pNtrC , pTorR , pUhpA , pYehT , and pYfhA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15522865" target="_blank">15522865</a>]<br></li>
<li>ArcB Transmitter Module TransphosphorylatesArcA , and the Activity Is Inhibited by Its Own Non-phosphorylated Re-ceiverDomain-I next analyzed the transphosphorylation activity of ArcB and its mutant proteins using a membrane preparation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8226939" target="_blank">8226939</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since these observations were made in both the presence ( 5 mM ) and the absence of IPTG , it appears that LacImediated repression of the phage T5 promoter of pQE30ArcA is incomplete in cells which also harbor either the pREP4 or q pACYC184lacI plasmid ( both of which constitutively express the lacI gene ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8892825" target="_blank">8892825</a>]<br></li>
