<li>The fact that the control of this promoter was independent of ArcA and Fnr ( Table 4 ) suggests that the prior observation by Iuchi et al. ( 9 ) that an arcA mutant was elevated for a-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase activity when grown under anaerobic conditions is accounted for by the regulated expression of the sucAB genes from the upstream sdhC promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9209026" target="_blank">9209026</a>]<br></li>
