<li>The sensor ± regulator pair , ArcB ± ArcA , is responsible for the microaerobic activation of the cydAB operon , whereas the anaerobic regulator Fnr represses its expression in the absence of oxygen .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10998176" target="_blank">10998176</a>]<br></li>
<li>Maximal expression under intermediate ( microaerobic ) oxygen levels is achieved by the counterbalance of activation by phosphorylated ArcA and repression by H-NS under aerobic conditions and repression by Fnr under anaerobicity [ 60 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14638413" target="_blank">14638413</a>]<br></li>
