<li>Kinetic modelling indicated that ArcA and FNR behaviour could not explain the ndh transcript profile , leading to the identification of another TF , PdhR , as the source of the asymmetry .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22870390" target="_blank">22870390</a>]<br></li>
<li>In contrast , strong responses to anaerobiosis and glucose ( a source of pyruvate ) mediated by global regulators ( ArcA , FNR and CRP ) are likely to be less beneficial .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8057842" target="_blank">8057842</a>]<br></li>
