<li>Interestingly , after a first step of gel filtration , about half of the ArcA protein ( as evaluated by SDS-PAGE ) eluted in the void volume ( molecular weight is > 300000 ) remained active in footprinting assays , whereas the partially purified protein eluted in a single peak as a monomer , was inactive ( no footprint with an estimated concentration of ArcA of 30jig ml '' ' ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8412671" target="_blank">8412671</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , although it is risky to compare the effects of non-purified protein with those produced by purified protein , ArcA appears to be able to take the place of Fur easily , whereas Fur deplaces ArcA only with great difficulty .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8412671" target="_blank">8412671</a>]<br></li>
