<li>Summary Manganese superoxide dismutase ( the sodA gene product ) in Escherichia coli , is negatively regulated by two global regulators , ArcA ( aerobic-respiration control ) and Fur ( ferric uptake regulation ) , coupling its expression to aerobic metabolism and the intracellular iron pool .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8412671" target="_blank">8412671</a>]<br></li>
<li>Three global regulatory systems , Fnr , NarX/NarL , and ArcB/ArcA , control expression of operons encoding enzymes involved in respiration and fermentation in Escherichia coli ( 10 , 25 , 28 , 36 , 38 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8132465" target="_blank">8132465</a>]<br></li>
<li>In Escherichia coli two global transcriptional regulatory proteins , Crp and Cra , are known to control transcriptional responses to carbon availability [ 28 , 30 ] , while two other global regulators , Fnr and ArcA , control gene-expression in response to oxygen availability [ 14 , 15 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8824175" target="_blank">8824175</a>]<br></li>
<li>Upon phosphorylation , ArcA binds extensively across the ge-nome , regulating the expression of ~ 100 operons and acting predominantly as a global repressor of nonfermentative carbon oxidation pathways ( 4 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25161193" target="_blank">25161193</a>]<br></li>
<li>Consequently , contrary to its established role of directly activating acetate production , ArcA suppresses acetate uptake through the expression of acs in the long-lived lipA mutant .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20707605" target="_blank">20707605</a>]<br></li>
<li>While being an antagonist of S expression in log phase , ArcA cooperates with S in a positive feedback loop in stationary phase By acting as a repressor for rpoS transcription , ArcA plays an antagonistic role for S in exponentially growing cells .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16291649" target="_blank">16291649</a>]<br></li>
