<li>This anaerobic response is modulated by the ArcA protein , which functions as a repressor of mdh gene-expression under both aerobic and anaerobic conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7592446" target="_blank">7592446</a>]<br></li>
<li>In summary , the results presented here indicate that ArcA and Fnr regulatory proteins play a role in repression of the E. coli tpx gene under anaerobic growth conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10794600" target="_blank">10794600</a>]<br></li>
