<li>ArcA overproduced in crude extracts protected a particularly long stretch of DNA ( 65 bp ) in one step , suggesting that the 27kDa ArcA protein binds as a multimer .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8412671" target="_blank">8412671</a>]<br></li>
<li>To create pQE30ArcA , a 734-bp BamHI-PstI fragment of pBTKSArcA ( including the complete ArcA coding sequence ) was cloned between the corresponding sites of pQE30 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8892825" target="_blank">8892825</a>]<br></li>
<li>Our ﬁnding that an N-terminally His-tagged variant of ArcA failed to stabilize binding to DR3 suggests that the His tag speciﬁcally disrupts the mechanism needed to enhance the energetics of DR3 binding site occupancy .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25161193" target="_blank">25161193</a>]<br></li>
