<li>174 , No. 11 Anaerobic Induction of Pyruvate Formate-Lyase Gene E Is Mediated by the ArcA and FNR Proteins xpression GARY SAWERS * AND BERNHARD SUPPMANN Lehrstuhlftir Mikrobiologie der Universitat Munchen , Maria-Ward-Strasse la , 8000 Munich 19 , Gernany Received 16 December 1991/Accepted 26 March 1992 The pyruvate formate-lyase ( pfl ) gene of Escherichia coli is transcribed from seven promoters which are coordinately induced 12 - to 15-fold by anaerobiosis .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1592804" target="_blank">1592804</a>]<br></li>
<li>Anaerobic induction of each of these promoters requires FNR and ArcA ( 35 ) , and anaerobic expression is further increased by growth in media containing pyruvate ( 33 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8376324" target="_blank">8376324</a>]<br></li>
