<li>Therefore transcription products starting at a , b and c sites are twice as abundant as the transcription products starting at d , d' and e. Muitiple arcA transcription start sites ArcA autoactivates transcription from P ^ Park etai ( 1992 ) suggested that ArcA negatively regulates its own transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8022271" target="_blank">8022271</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is feasible that there may be severai ArcA recognition sequences located within this region of DNA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7565118" target="_blank">7565118</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is not yet known what DNA sequences are recognized by ArcA for binding to DNA and where it binds within the hemA regulatory region .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8071201" target="_blank">8071201</a>]<br></li>
<li>When activated anaerobically by the membrane sensor protein encoded by arcB , ArcA typically represses a number of operons of aerobic function ( Iuchi and Lin 1988 ; Iuchi et al. 1990b ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1851949" target="_blank">1851949</a>]<br></li>
<li>In parallel , the role of ArcA changes to that of an agonist of S , as it becomes part of a positive feedback that further stabilizes S ; arcA expression increases in a partially S-dependent manner ( Fig. 6A , B ) , and ArcA plays a positive role in S stabilization in starved cells ( Fig. 6C ) , as even small increases in ArcA concentration efficiently interfere with RssB phosphorylation by ArcB ( especially when phosphorylated ArcB is in reduced supply as in cells that enter into an energy starvation situation ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16291649" target="_blank">16291649</a>]<br></li>
<li>Therefore , it is not possible to locate potential ArcA-binding sites by sequence analysis , although it is presumed that dctA is directly repressed by ArcA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10482502" target="_blank">10482502</a>]<br></li>
<li>For example , most of the genes in group III are repressed by the O2-sensing system mediated by ArcA ( 49 , 70 ) , and although not directly demonstrated , the data in this paper suggest that these genes can also be repressed by FNR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15659690" target="_blank">15659690</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furthermore , despite being repressed by FNR and ArcA ( 22 ) , fumA did not meet the criteria set for responsive transcripts at any of the time points .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16857675" target="_blank">16857675</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is now apparent from studies with the corresponding l a c 2 fusions that the fumA promoter resembles PacnBin being anaerobically repressed by ArcA , whereas the fumC promoter resembles P2acnAin its dual regulation by ArcA and FNR , although there is evidence that fumC transcription is partially facilitated by readthrough from the upstream fumA gene promoter ( Woods & Guest , 1987 ; Guest & Russell , 1992 ; Gruer & Guest , 1994 ; Park & Gunsalus , 1995 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9421904" target="_blank">9421904</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expressionfrom the suc promoter was repressed by IHF and partially activated by d8but it was not regulated by ArcA , FNR , CRP , FruR or Fis , and not repressed by glucose or anaerobiosis , indicating that the well-established catabolite and anaerobic repression of ODH synthesis is imposed elsewhere .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9720032" target="_blank">9720032</a>]<br></li>
<li>Incontrast , the / pel promoter was repressed by both glucose ( via a CRP-independentmechanism ) and anaerobiosis ( mediated by ArcA ) , and activated by Fis , but it was not regulated by FNR , FruR , IHF or These observations support the view that transcription of the sucABCD genes is primarily initiated and regulated at the upstream sdh promoter , and that the Ipd promoter is independently co-regulated with Pdh ( primarily by ArcAmediated repression ) rather than with PsucDirect evidence for co-transcription of the entire sdhCDAksucABCD region from PHNw t as obtained by detecting a 10 kb transcript inm c and me mutants , but not inthe parental strains .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9720032" target="_blank">9720032</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results indicate that repression by nitrate is independent of the three transcription factors ArcA , IHF , and FNR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7601827" target="_blank">7601827</a>]<br></li>
<li>When iron becomes scarce , Fur becomes inactive , resulting in derepression of sodA transcription ; however , only under conditions in which FNR and ArcA are inactive ( i.e. in presence of O2 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20075074" target="_blank">20075074</a>]<br></li>
<li>Note , however , that this group also includes sodA ( 6.7-fold induction ) , which is regulated by FNR and other transcription factors , and cyoA , which is known to be repressed by ArcA during anaerobic growth .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16377617" target="_blank">16377617</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although the transcription factor MarA is not directly regulated by FNR or ArcA , four genes that are activated by MarA ( acnA , fumC , sodA , zwf ) are repressed by ArcA and/or FNR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23980183" target="_blank">23980183</a>]<br></li>
<li>In contrast , acnB expression is activated by CRP and repressed by ArcA , FruR and Fis from PacnBC .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9421904" target="_blank">9421904</a>]<br></li>
<li>Regulation of acnB gene transcription Apart from being activated by CRP and repressed by ArcA , the acnB gene exhibited a very different pattern of regulation to that of acnA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9421904" target="_blank">9421904</a>]<br></li>
<li>Further studies with acn-lac2 gene fusions and a wider range of transcription regulators indicated that acnA expression is initiated by G ~ ~ from PIacnAa , nd from PZacnA it is activated directly or indirectly by CRP , FruR , Fur and SoxRS , and repressed by ArcA and FNR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9421904" target="_blank">9421904</a>]<br></li>
<li>This showed that the acnB gene is subject to repression by ArcA , Fis and FruR and activation by CRP , whereas the a c n A gene is repressed by ArcA and FNR , activated by FruR , CRP , Fur and SoxRS , and initiated by a38in stationary phase .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9421904" target="_blank">9421904</a>]<br></li>
<li>These confirmed that the acnA gene resembles other citric acid cycle genes in being positively regulated by the CAMP-CRP complex and negatively regulated by ArcA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8000525" target="_blank">8000525</a>]<br></li>
<li>The majority of other ArcA or FNR regulated genes studied so far are either repressed anaerobically by ArcA or activated anaerobically by FNR , although three examples are known whose expression is repressed by FNR anaerobically ( 14 , 24 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1592804" target="_blank">1592804</a>]<br></li>
<li>The responses obtained with the fusion indicated that ArcA functions as an anaerobic repressor acnB acnB of transcription and that the gene is not regulated by FNR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9421904" target="_blank">9421904</a>]<br></li>
<li>The acnA gene is positively regulated by Crp , SoxRS , FNR and repressed by ArcA [ 59 ] , whereas acnB is positively regulated by CRP and negatively regulated by ArcA , FruR and Fis .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22513097" target="_blank">22513097</a>]<br></li>
<li>The fumB gene is positively regulated by FNR , ArcA , Crp and Fur and negatively by Fis and NarL .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22513097" target="_blank">22513097</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of hya is induced by anaerobiosis and repressed by nitrate ( 9 ) and requires the sigma factor RpoS ( 2 ) and the transcriptional regulators ArcA and AppY ( 9 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10464194" target="_blank">10464194</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription from P5 was not significantly affected by ArcA under any condition .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11123679" target="_blank">11123679</a>]<br></li>
<li>As shown in Figure 7 , as expected , transcription of PicdA-lacZ and PlpdA-lacZ fusions were signiﬁcantly repressed by ArcA under anaerobic condition , since arcA caused de-repression of their transcription under anaerobic condition in M9 glucose medium , the same condition used in this study .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23874328" target="_blank">23874328</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition to CRP and NAC , feaR may also be repressed by PhoB ( 20 ) and ArcA ( P. J. Kiley , personal communication ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24013633" target="_blank">24013633</a>]<br></li>
<li>P1icdA was repressed 14-fold by ArcA ( Fig. 3A ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25161193" target="_blank">25161193</a>]<br></li>
<li>In good agreement with the in vivo observations ( see Fig. 3 ) , transcription of ssb was also repressed by ArcA ( Fig. 4 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16140472" target="_blank">16140472</a>]<br></li>
<li>For example , all the fad genes repressed by FadR are also repressed by the ArcA transcription factor ( encoded by arcA ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23026122" target="_blank">23026122</a>]<br></li>
<li>We observed signiﬁcant downregulation of the sdhABCD ( succinate dehydrogenase ) and frdABCD operons , known to be repressed by ArcA , under oxic conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20709841" target="_blank">20709841</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the absence of oxygen , ArcA is bound to its cognate sites acting to repress transcription of the fad regulon genes , even under non-inducing conditions ( without fatty-acids ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16849788" target="_blank">16849788</a>]<br></li>
<li>More recently , another transcription factor , IscR , has been shown to directly repress the hyaA promoter ( PhyaA ) but only under aerobic conditions when ArcA and AppY are not active ( 14 , 28 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23065979" target="_blank">23065979</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of both of these operons has been shown to be induced under low-oxygen conditions ( 8 , 9 ) and to be activated by the ArcA transcription factor ( 3 , 8 ) ( Table 1 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19734316" target="_blank">19734316</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , it is not surprising that ArcA , which is active under conditions of oxygen limitation , is an activator of moe operon transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11357510" target="_blank">11357510</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , it appears that ArcA , either directly or indirectly , negatively regulates the transcription of the anaerobic b-oxidation pathway genes fadJ and fadI in the absence of oxygen .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16849788" target="_blank">16849788</a>]<br></li>
<li>Direct in vivo binding of ArcA to the upstream regions of anaerobic b-oxidative genes in the absence of oxygen The transcript levels of fadJ and fadI indicate that ArcA negatively regulates their expression in response to oxygen limitation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16849788" target="_blank">16849788</a>]<br></li>
<li>Only two of these genes , nuoG and nuoF , are known members of the ArcA regulon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15699038" target="_blank">15699038</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression Pattern II : Increased Expression during Anaerobiosis and Decreased Expression in an ArcA Strain -- Transcription of the 57 genes of expression pattern II ( Table II ) was both induced in the absence of oxygen and positively regulated by ArcA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15699038" target="_blank">15699038</a>]<br></li>
<li>The gltA , acnA , and mdh genes appear to be controlled by ArcA only ( 11 , 29 , 30 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7592392" target="_blank">7592392</a>]<br></li>
<li>The two genes reported to be regulated by oxygen and/or ArcA are fumB and lysU .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15699038" target="_blank">15699038</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , the sucABCD genes are negatively regulated by both the ArcA and Fnr proteins .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9209026" target="_blank">9209026</a>]<br></li>
<li>The number of genes found to be regulated both by ArcA and Fnr is growing .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8022271" target="_blank">8022271</a>]<br></li>
<li>Recent lacZ transcriptional fusion experiments in our laboratory confirm these results and further demonstrate that these genes are regulated by ArcA but , 3 as reported here , not by FNR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12754220" target="_blank">12754220</a>]<br></li>
<li>Two other genes , rhaA ( L-rhamnose isomer-ase ) and glgC ( glucose-1-phosphate adenylyltransferase ) , have not been shown previously to be regulated by ArcA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15699038" target="_blank">15699038</a>]<br></li>
<li>There are also dual effects of Fnr and ArcA which can not be completely explained by arcA regulation and suggest functional Fnr-ArcA interactions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8022271" target="_blank">8022271</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of the E. cofipfloperon is induced by anae-robiosis ( Sawers and B6ck , 1988 ; 1989 ) and regulation is mediated by Fnr functioning in conjunction with the ArcA transcription factor ( for a review see luchi and Lin , 1993 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8709852" target="_blank">8709852</a>]<br></li>
<li>Data from Cotter and Gunsalus ( 1992 ) showing that fnr transcription is not activated by ArcA seem to exclude an indirect effect mediated by Fnr , It is possible that there is an ArcA feedback loop , but only when a threshold concentration of ArcA protein is reached .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8022271" target="_blank">8022271</a>]<br></li>
<li>Negative regulation of ssb transcription by ArcA The ssb gene encoding single-strand DNA-binding protein is located next to uvrA but transcribed in the opposite direction ( see Fig. 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16140472" target="_blank">16140472</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , ArcA has also been reported to activate transcription of some genes , for example , the cydAB operon of E. coli and the cob genes of Salmonella typhimurium [ 34,35 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9716493" target="_blank">9716493</a>]<br></li>
<li>Anaerobic activation of arcA promoter aerobically , whilst the pfl gene is transcribed transcription in Escherichia coli : roles of Fnr and ArcA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9084161" target="_blank">9084161</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , in the absence of Fnr , ArcA was not able to induce transcription from P ^ .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8022271" target="_blank">8022271</a>]<br></li>
<li>Whereas the fumA promoter is regulated by both Fnr and ArcA , transcription from the fumC promoter is regulated by ArcA and SoxR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7592392" target="_blank">7592392</a>]<br></li>
<li>The mechanism by which ArcA suppresses the transcription of acs is therefore unclear .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20707605" target="_blank">20707605</a>]<br></li>
<li>In vitro transcription assays showed that phospho-ArcA ( ArcA-P ) represses ptsG P1 transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15252051" target="_blank">15252051</a>]<br></li>
<li>ArcA represses rpoS transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16291649" target="_blank">16291649</a>]<br></li>
