<li>TorC autoregulation is different from tor anaerobic control The torCAD operon is fully induced in anaerobiosis but , in contrast to all other known anaerobic respiratory systems , this control is mediated neither by FNR , a pleiotropic anae-robic regulator , nor by ArcA , a response regulator involved in redox control of numerous genes ( Simon et al. , 1994 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10411745" target="_blank">10411745</a>]<br></li>
<li>The anaerobic fumarase , encoded by fumB , is known to be activated during anaerobic fermentative growth ( 50 , 51 ) , and Tseng ( 51 ) showed that both ArcA and FNR are responsible for this anaerobic activation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15699038" target="_blank">15699038</a>]<br></li>
