<li>Since anaerobic induction of the hydrogenase 1 operon ( 9 ) and the acid phosphatase operon ( 1 ) ( Table 2 ) is dependent on both AppY and ArcA , we investigated whether anaerobic induction of the appY gene was regulated by ArcA or was auto-regulated .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8626281" target="_blank">8626281</a>]<br></li>
<li>The expression of the appY gene is induced immediately by anaerobiosis , and this anaerobic induction is independent of Fnr , and AppY , but dependent on ArcA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8626281" target="_blank">8626281</a>]<br></li>
