<li>ArcA and AppY Antagonize IscR Repression of Hydrogenase-1 Expression under Anaerobic Conditions , Revealing a Novel Mode O2 Regulation of Gene Expression in Escherichia coli of A. D. Nesbit , * A. S. Fleischhacker , S. J. Teter , and P. J. Kiley Department of Biomolecular Chemistry , University of Wisconsin , Madison , Wisconsin , USA Transcription of the Escherichia coli hydrogenase-1 operon ( hyaABCDEF ) is increased by the transcription factors ArcA and AppY under anaerobic growth conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23065979" target="_blank">23065979</a>]<br></li>
<li>The anaerobic transcription of the hydrogenase 1 operon is activated by ArcA and AppY , which seem to act independently .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8626281" target="_blank">8626281</a>]<br></li>
<li>ArcA and AppY activated transcription of the cyx-appA operon during entry into stationary phase and under anaerobic growth conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8626281" target="_blank">8626281</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results indicate that both AppY and ArcA are involved in activating the transcription of the hya operon during anaerobic growth .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8071220" target="_blank">8071220</a>]<br></li>
<li>During anaerobic growth , ArcA represses transcription of several genes involved in aerobic metabolism , including the cyo operon ( 23 ) , and activates transcription of the pfl gene ( 35 ) and the cyd operon ( 15 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8071219" target="_blank">8071219</a>]<br></li>
<li>During anaerobic growth , ArcA represses transcription of several genes involved in aerobic metabolism ( 17 ) and activates transcription of the pyruvate formate-lyase ( pfl ) gene ( 30 ) as well as the cytochrome d oxidase ( cydAB ) operon ( 15 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8071220" target="_blank">8071220</a>]<br></li>
<li>In those studies , it was suggested that ArcA represses fadK transcription under anaerobic conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16849788" target="_blank">16849788</a>]<br></li>
<li>ArcA is the major regulator of aerobic metabolism and represses the genes of aerobic metabolism under anaerobic conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9230919" target="_blank">9230919</a>]<br></li>
<li>ArcA appears to repress mdh transcription under both aerobic and anaerobic conditions , as has also been shown for the gltA and sdhCDAB TCA genes ( 16 , 17 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7592446" target="_blank">7592446</a>]<br></li>
