<li>This allows peak gene expression and subsequent repression by Fnr Summary The Escherichia coli cydAB operon , encoding the subunits of the high-affinity cytochrome d oxidase , is maximally transcribed in microaerobiosis as a result of the combined action of the oxygen-responsive regulators Fnr and ArcA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11123679" target="_blank">11123679</a>]<br></li>
